Prevention Checklist

✅ Do’s

• Always verify the receiver’s name before sending money
• Check carefully whether it is a “Pay” or “Collect” request
• Use trusted apps like Google Pay, PhonePe, and Paytm
• Enable transaction alerts (SMS/email) for instant updates
• Keep your UPI apps and mobile software updated
• Use strong passwords, PIN, or biometric lock on your phone
• Report fraud immediately to your bank and Cyber Crime Portal India

❌ Don’ts

• Don’t enter your UPI PIN to receive money
• Don’t share OTP, UPI PIN, or bank details with anyone
• Don’t click on unknown or suspicious links
• Don’t scan QR codes from unknown sources
• Don’t trust strangers asking for urgent payments
• Don’t install apps from untrusted websites
• Don’t ignore small suspicious transactions